## File Structure
1. Name files: `YYYY-MM-DD-kebab-case-title.md`
2. Place in `blog/content/` directory

## Frontmatter Format
```yaml
---
layout: post
title: "Your Title Here"
date: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS -0600
categories:
  - category1
  - category2
provenance:  # Added after initial commit
  repo: "https://github.com/frison/agentt"
  commit: "commit-sha-here"
---
```

## Content Guidelines
1. Use markdown for content
2. Structure with H2 (`##`) for main sections
3. Include code blocks with language specification
4. End with provenance statement after commit

## Required Sections
1. Introduction (no heading)
2. Main content sections (H2)
3. Conclusion section (H2)
4. Provenance footer (after commit)

## Process
1. Create post with initial frontmatter
2. Write content following guidelines
3. Commit post
4. Add provenance information
5. Commit provenance update